article.description: — Steele Venters had 18 points and eight rebounds as Eastern Washington beat Northern Arizona 69-62 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Venters leads E. Washington past N. Arizona 69-62
article.linkText: Venters leads E. Washington past N. Arizona 69-62
article.story: CHENEY, Wash. -- — Steele Venters had 18 points and eight rebounds as Eastern Washington beat Northern Arizona 69-62 on Thursday night. Ethan Price had 13 points for Eastern Washington (16-14, 10-9 Big Sky Conference), which earned its fourth consecutive home victory. Rylan Bergersen added 12 points. Linton Acliese III had 10 points. Keith Haymon scored a career-high 24 points for the Lumberjacks (9-21, 5-14), who have now lost six consecutive games. Jalen Cone added 20 points. Carson Towt had 11 rebounds and six assists. The Eagles improve to 2-0 against the Lumberjacks on the season. Eastern Washington defeated Northern Arizona 78-65 on Jan. 1. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
